

Java 10 Features (Interview Important)

Java 10 mainly focused on developer productivity and JVM improvements. The most important feature is var (Local Variable Type Inference).

1. var (Local Variable Type Inference) ⭐
.....................................
.....................................
Java 10 allows the compiler to automatically infer the type.

Example
Before Java 10
String name = "Sunil";
List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
Java 10
var name = "Sunil";
var list = new ArrayList<String>();
Real Example
var age = 25;
var salary = 50000.50;

System.out.println(age);
System.out.println(salary);
Rules of var

✔ Can be used only for local variables
✔ Must be initialized at declaration
✔ Cannot be used for method parameters
✔ Cannot be used for class fields

Invalid Example ❌
var name; // ❌ Not allowed
2. Garbage Collection Improvements
...........................................
..............................................
Java 10 improved GC performance (especially G1 GC).

Example (Conceptual)

Better memory handling for large applications:

Less pause time
Faster memory cleanup
3. Application Class-Data Sharing (AppCDS)
.................................................
Improves startup time and memory footprint.

Benefit
Faster JVM startup
Reduced memory usage
4. Parallel Full GC for G1
...........................................
Improves performance in large heap applications.

Benefit
Faster garbage collection
Better throughput in enterprise apps
5. Time-Based Release Versioning
...............................
Java moved to 6-month release cycle.

Example
Java 10 = March 2018 release
Java 11 = September 2018
Real-Time Example (Spring Boot)
Using var in Service Layer
@Service
public class EmployeeService {

    public void process() {

        var employee = new Employee();
        var list = new ArrayList<Employee>();

        list.add(employee);
    }
}
When NOT to use var

❌ Complex code readability issues

var data = getData(); // unclear type
Interview Summary
Feature	Description
var	Local variable type inference
